collections.name: Pareidolia Art
collections.description:
Artist: Samantha Rhaye Madison McKa
Medium: Digital Pareidolia Illustration

"Chaos in the Deep" is a visual odyssey born from the subconscious, where hidden figures emerge from the tangle of lines and shadows. This piece is part of my pareidolia art—an intuitive process where I begin with abstract squiggles, allowing the shapes to reveal themselves to me. I listen to the lines, following where they lead, uncovering forms that exist within the chaos.

In this piece, the city is alive with a symphony of figures—some human, some animal, some unearthly. A pregnant woman stands among the vastness embodying creation amid disorder. A whale drifts through the scene, as if navigating an ocean of unrest. A dog is caught in the wind, its fur swept by unseen forces. Faces emerge, whispering stories of the city’s hidden spirits. Monsters lurk, some playful, some menacing, each woven into the dark, flowing fabric of the composition.

collections.name: space nymph abnormalities
collections.description:
A fusion of ethereal beauty and biomechanical transcendence, Nymph Abnormalities is a visionary NFT collection exploring the evolution of divine beings beyond the boundaries of nature. These cosmic nymphs are no longer tied to forests and rivers; they have been reconstructed through technology, infused with celestial energy, and reborn as anomalies of the universe.

Each entity in this collection is a hybrid of organic divinity and synthetic augmentation, their forms both mesmerizing and surreal, adorned with metallic bioware, luminous halos, and intricate circuitry. They defy symmetry, transcend mortal limitations, and exist in a realm where gods are engineered and spirits are rewired.

collections.name: ETO dots
collections.description:
In Japan there is a culture that came from China called "ETO".
This is a system in which 12 different creatures are assigned according to the year of birth.
The 12 creatures are rat, cow(ox), tiger, rabbit, dragon, snake, horse, sheep, monkey, chicken, dog, and boar.
By the way, the year 2025 will be the year of the snake.

Please try to find the "ETO" that corresponds to your year of birth.

The “ETO” goes around in a 12-year cycle
Year of the Rat: 1936, 1948, ..., 2020
Year of the Ox: 1937, 1949, ..., 2021
Year of the Tiger: 1938, 1950, ..., 2022
Year of the Rabbit: 1939, 1951, ..., 2023
Year of the Dragon: 1940, 1952, ..., 2024
Year of the Snake: 1941, 1953, ..., 2025
Year of the Horse: 1942, 1954, ..., 2014
Year of the Sheep: 1943, 1955, ..., 2015
Year of the Monkey: 1944, 1956, ..., 2016
Year of the Chicken: 1945, 1957, ..., 2017
Year of the Dog: 1946, 1958, ..., 2018
Year of the Wild Boar: 1947, 1959, ..., 2019
